title: Ayla Connectivity GATT Service
description: This document defines the Ayla Connectivity GATT Service profile, implementation, and uses.

title: Ayla Customer Dashboard User Guide
description: This document provides information on how to use the Ayla Customer Dashboard. This dashboard allows you to manage your deployment of Ayla Connected Products.

title: Ayla Data Export Feature for Device Events
description: This document explains how to use the Ayla Data Export feature, and provides the formats of the expected event data files.

title: Ayla Data Retention Policies
description: This document describes Ayla’s Data Retention policy and options including where you can access your data, how long it is retained in our systems, and options to extend the length of time your data is stored.

title: Ayla DDoS Mitigation and Protection
description: This document describes the defenses employed in the Ayla Cloud for DDoS attacks.

title: Ayla Developer Portal User Guide
description: This document provides information on how to use the Ayla Developer Portal to manage and configure your Ayla Connected products.

title: Ayla Device Wi-Fi for Embedded Systems
description: This document provides information on the design and implementation of the Ayla Device Wi-Fi (ADW) software for use in embedded microprocessor systems. You may use this document as a specification for the features, algorithms, software interfaces, and integration considerations when using ADW.

title: Ayla DSN Reservation Process
description: Ayla DSN reservation allows module manufacturers to put aside DSNs for future use. This document describes the process of reserving and using reserves DSNs.

title: Ayla Embedded Agent for Android
description: The Ayla Embedded Agent for Android is a software development framework that allows a device running Android OS to access the Ayla Cloud Service using an Android application, calling Ayla’s device API. The Android Agent software distribution contains the API libraries and a ready-to-run Android sample application, which can be used as a reference.

title: Ayla Embedded Agent for Embedded Systems
description: The Ayla Embedded Agent enables modules to connect to the Ayla Cloud Services using a white box, integrated development model.

title: Ayla Embedded Agent for Marvell HAP SDK
description: This document describes the installation and use of the Ayla Embedded Agent software on modules using Marvell HAP SDK

title: Ayla Embedded Agent for Marvell WMSDK
description: This document describes the installation and use of the Ayla Embedded Agent software on modules using the Marvell WMSDK.

title: Ayla Embedded Agent for QCA4010
description: This document describes the installation and use of the Ayla Embedded Agent software on modules using Qualcomm QCA4010 or QCA4012 SDK.

title: Ayla Factory Service API Specification
description: The Ayla Factory Service (AFS) is used to create device-specific data required for normal operation of the embedded device agent client provided by Ayla.

title: Ayla Generic GATT Service
description: This document defines the Ayla Generic GATT Service Profile, registered with Bluetooth SIG under the name of Ayla Networks. This will guarantee an official, universally global Ayla UUID, which can be identified by clients. Furthermore, this will allow clients to assume a certain subset of custom profiles and functionality, supported by Ayla enabled devices.

title: Ayla Insights
description: Ayla Insights is a fully-integrated business intelligence platform that provides Ayla customers with real-world insights into how their connected products are being used. Insights provides an easy path for customers to unlock the value of their data by offering a way to visualize, analyze, and explore their data quickly, regardless of the device type. The Insights data platform completes the feedback loop for manufacturers and provides the fastest path for uncovering the actionable data needed to improve product development, customer satisfaction, and revenues.

title: Ayla Intelligent Over-The-Air Solution
description: Ayla Over-the-Air (OTA) solution provides real-time and scheduled management and services for up to 1 million devices at a time. OTA enables manufacturers to securely send device firmware updates to devices in both development and field environments. This is often required for updates needed in the communications protocol and for improvements to product functionality and in the transport or security service.

title: Ayla LAN Mode Mobile
description: This document provides a high-level overview of how to use LAN Mode in mobile applications.

title: Ayla Local Devices Developers Guide
description: This document is directed towards mobile application developers who are writing an Aylaconnected mobile application that interoperates with devices that do not have their own persistent connection to the internet.

title: Ayla Manufacturing Guide
description: This document describes the manufacturing steps required to build a solution with an Ayla production module. It also describes the steps required to move from an Ayla Development environment to an Ayla Field Service.

title: Ayla Mobile Getting Started
description: The Ayla Mobile SDK provides Ayla customers a powerful set of tools for building mobile applications integrated with the Ayla Cloud Service. Designed for both iOS and Android platforms, the Ayla Mobile SDK lets app developer’s focus on the app details instead of data management or network communication, leading to a faster time to market and a more solid application.

title: Ayla Mobile SDK Developers Guide
description: The Ayla Mobile SDK is designed to provide mobile application developers on the iOS and Android platforms a way to easily interact with the Ayla Cloud Service and connected devices.

title: Ayla Registration Methods
description: Ayla Networks provides OEM customers with a choice of five different registration methods. The registration methods bind the device to the user application based on the priorities and conditions that the OEM defined for the product (devices). These methods serve as an additional level of security for connected devices.

title: Ayla RBAC API Specification
description: This document presents an overview of the Role Based Access Control (RBAC) system including administrative and operational tasks.

title: Ayla Rules API Specification
description: This document describes the Ayla Rules Engine API.

title: Ayla Schedules
description: Schedules are a common, sometimes underestimated, feature in many home appliance and other consumer products that play an essential role in the long-term ownership experience of a product. Ayla provides our customers with the ability to develop schedules for all connected devices built on Ayla’s IoT platform.

title: Ayla Service API Specification
description: This document describes the APIs that are used to access the Ayla Cloud Service (ACS).

title: Ayla Single Sign-on
description: This document provides the Ayla platform interfaces to integrate with external identity providers for user account management.

title: Boot Loader Framework User Guide
description: This guide introduces you to the OTA related tool chain, such as the image packager utility and embedded MCU bootloader.

title: Connection History Overview
description: Ayla devices communicate with two services in the Ayla Cloud: Ayla Notification Service (ANS) and Ayla Device Service (ADS). Devices uses UDP keep-alive packets to communicate with ANS which maintains the device online/offline state. ANS communicates these states with ADS. ANS notifies the device of any pending data or commands for the device. The device communicates with HTTPS to ADS to send property updates or receive property updates and commands. The device connection status can be seen in the OEM Dashboard.

title: Creating an App ID-Secret Pair
description: This document explains how to create an AppId/AppSecret pair.

title: Customize Notification Messages
description: This document describes how to customize Email notifications as well as modify notifications on Ayla templates.

title: Device OEM Domain Transfer
description: Ayla technology partners should review this document before transferring their Design Kitbased devices from the default domain (which the device is originally associated with) to the private OEM domain assigned to their organization. There are important specifications and procedures to follow to ensure a successful transfer.

title: Host OTA Instructions User Guide

title: Ayla ESP32 Solution
description: The Ayla ESP32 Solution includes example host application source code, an Ayla Wi-Fi Integrated Agent, and Ayla extensions to the Espressif IoT Development Framework (IDF)

title: Ayla Portable Solution
description: The Ayla Portable Solution consists of software libraries not tied to any specific communication module SDK or chipset. It enables OEMs to extend Ayla connectivity to communication modules not supported by Ayla Integrated Agents.

title: Ayla Datastream Service
description: The Ayla Datastream Service (DSS) is a WebSocket server that pushes device-related event notifications (in near real-time) from the Ayla Cloud to subscribing WebSocket clients.
